column5: Hi all, My name is Julio and i'm new to the forum and to fishing. I started fishing this year and i'm hooked... I've been fishing mostly urban areas around mississauga and the gta and for the most part i've targeted bass. I'm now living in London for the next two years and hope to get some fishing done soon in the area. I'm looking forward to contributing to the forum, which has been a great resource for me Here's a couple of pics from the summer..  A smallmouth   A small carp   Cheers, Julio
Welcome to OFC Julio Good looking pics Looking forward to reading your future reports!!! Leechman
welcome julio, gotta be some water around London somewhere you can fish, let us know how you do
Welcome aboard Julio ...the Thames River is going to be your friend ...enjoy it for all the species it has to offer ...i know it fairly well so if any questions ...shoot away ...
Thanks for your replies. Ill be giving the Thames a try soon and ill post a report when i do...
Welcome!  I'm kind of new myself. Have been reading lots here, but not been to active!  Have to say - It's an amazing forum with tons of knowledge and help to get.  Enjoy!
WELCOME ABOARD THE BOARD!!!!!!!!!!!!!  TONS of insight here and lotsa  GREAT people... enjoy the company.   RFS
Hang on to yer hat me son.It,s a wild ride here WELCOME
Hey I've got 2 of those Rapala Husky Rods. They are great. (Although I hit one off the ground in a fit of rage and the tip snapped off.. lol)
Yeah this one has been pretty good, i might be looking to get another rod for next year (mostly for bass), any suggestions?  thanks

I picked up a shimano claraus rod this year and I have been really happy with it and it was under $100 taxes in .  welcome to the board if your new to the london area there's lots of fishing in and around the city .
BTW wait till the fishing show at the western fair grounds if it's for next year lots of good deals think it's in feb.
Sounds good thanks, i'll check it out!
